SIMPLE: indistinction
RECORDS: 1

==== ENTRY 1 ====
HEADWORD: Indistinction
<hw>In`dis*tinc"tion</hw>
<pr>(⟦icr⟧n`d⟦icr⟧s*t⟦icr⟧⟦nsm⟧k"sh⟦ucr⟧n)</pr>, <pos>n.</pos> <ety>[Cf.
F. <ets>indistinction</ets>.]</ety> <def>Lack of distinction or
distinguishableness; confusion; uncertainty; indiscrimination.</def>⟦br⟧
[<source>1913 Webster</source>]</p>

<p><q>The <qex>indistinction</qex> of many of the same name . . . hath
made some doubt.</q> <rj><qau>Sir T. Browne.</qau></rj>⟦br⟧
[<source>1913 Webster</source>]</p>

<p><q>An <qex>indistinction</qex> of all persons, or equality of all
orders, is far from being agreeable to the will of God.</q>
<rj><qau>Sprat.</qau></rj>⟦br⟧
[<source>1913 Webster</source>]</p>

<p><ent>Indistinctive</ent>⟦br⟧
